| shelySQL 1.0 requirements 			|
+===============================================+
| Kernel: Linuzx 4.18.0-425.3.1.el8.x86_64	|			
| zenity version 3.28.1				|
+===============================================+

+===============================+
| how to use 			|
+===============================+
| - use source of RDBMS file	|  
| - and enjoy 			| 
+===============================+

+=======================================================+
| graphical & qeury statment RDBMS program overview	|
+=======================================================+
| => Database tools (Graphical & Query statement) <=	|
| - create database					|
| - use database					|
| - drop database					|
| - create users for database				|
|							|
| => table tools (Graphical & Query statement) <=	|
| - create table (Grapical only)			|
| - drop table						|
| - insert into table					|
| - add primary key					|
| - data type (string - int)				|
| - update values					|
| 							|
| => another behinded functions <=			|
| - check is database exist or not			|
| - check is table exist or not				|
| - check is column exist or not			|
| - check is primary exist in table or not		|
| - check is string is =~ with his column or not	|
+=======================================================+

+===============================+
|            examples           |
+===============================+
========> drop statment <========
drop table tableName
drop database dataBaseName

========> drop statment <========
#create statment
create table tableName
create database dataBaseName

========> drop statment <========
#use statment
use dataBaseName

========> drop statment <========
#select statment
select * from table
select COUNT from table
select col1 col2 from table

========> alter statment <========
alter table tableName add column columnName datatype size ( primary-not )
alter table tableName delete column columnName

========> select statment with where condition <========
select * from table where id = 5
select COUNT from table where id = 5
select col1 col2 from table where col2 = "name"

========> delete statment <========
delete from table where col1="name"

========> update statment <========
update table set col1 = "value" Where col2 = "val"

========> insert statment <========
insert into table values valForCol1 , valForCol1



















